Todd M. Sechrist 

		
		EVP and COO, 

	
		 EnerSys Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 05/23/2017 



Executive Summary
Todd Sechrist serves as the Chief Operating Officer of EnerSys Inc., a Bern Township, Pennsylvania-based manufacturer of batteries, chargers and accessories for motive, reserve, aerospace and defense applications. Just three months prior to his promotion to his current role, in January 2016, he was elevated to Executive Vice Presi 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Sechrist married Stacey in 1989. They live with their children in Reinholds, Pennsylvania.
Sechrist graduated from Wilson High School in 1984. 
Current Focus

Company Snapshot: EnerSys Inc., the global leader in stored energy solutions for industrial applications, manufactures and distributes reserve power and motive power batteries, battery chargers, power equipment, battery 
Key Challenges

Rising Prices: “During the fourth quarter our global lead cost will continue to rise sequentially and year-over-year by over 10%,” CEO David Shaffer told analysts on the company’s February 2017 earning 
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1966 in West Lawn, Pennsylvania.
Sechrist earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Finance from Pennsylvania State University in 1988. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Board of Directors, EUROBAT

 





